The menu of a fat-hungry child: It does not eat breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have problems with obesity, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have shown that obese children are mostly from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important the environment is for the healthy development of a human being, in which he grows up and are the examples that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more frequently on the table than in families where normal - weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had fries for dinner on the day before the educational campaign under the motto "Adiposity is not a coincidence".
In families with fat children, sport is also not one of the favourite activities, which also affects the majority of today's students - only 15 percent replied that their parents find time for active movement at least once a week.
Survey among 900 children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, with nearly 900 children from primary schools throughout the Czech Republic being surveyed.
This was already the second year of the "Adiposity is not a coincidence" campaign, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Fund and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12 thousand students from 4th and 8th classes have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are decisive factors that are responsible for the horrifying increase in the number of children with overweight or even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed, for example, said eating breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-vesper dinner five times a day - one of the main requirements for a healthy diet," one of the survey results says.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that relative small things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are also important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the students' families have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone has breakfast for themselves.
Worst of all was the finding that in every tenth family there is no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is considered to be the cornerstone of a healthy daily diet.
Among other things, the survey test revealed that in the families of overweight children people often consume unhealthy fries.
And almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
While more than 40 percent of the children surveyed exercise, only less than half of their parents do so - only 15 percent.
Set up your own menu
Another part of the survey made it possible for selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compile their own meal plan from the possibilities offered by appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many flours, meat dishes and, of course, desserts.
"Alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet lemonades", is emphasized in the final report to this survey.
At lunch, i.e. the main course, pasta was victorious just before poultry.
The children almost didn't like legumes and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Returning to Health
At the same time, however, the survey also showed that children are quite willing to change their eating habits when they get the right information.
"In the control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after completing the enlightening presentation "Adiposity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a marked shift in preferences towards principles of healthy nutrition", the results of the project are quoted.
This was eye-catching, for example, with the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also crossed poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire as the main course of the day and were ready to eat less dumplings or sweet food.
Professionals claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article about how stylists learn, I had a bit moaned that this was a bit too much stuff for the beginning.
I didn't know in the least what else was coming.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar on how the "on the square" works.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer the test approaches, the more information and practical tasks are ahead of us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully occupied.
This time we debated with Director Alena (not a single man participates in the course) how to attract a woman who does not have an ideal proportional figure.
And that's what most of us are.
Some have one too short neck, the others have a too young figure without proper curves and others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to optically cover wide shoulders, extend the neck or conjure up the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to attract a female type like Jennifer Lopez - i.e. with a large bust, wide hip and narrow waist - pretty and figure-stressed, without making her seem too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so big that the skirt or pants really don't fit, you should at least have a piece tailored to your needs.
You won't regret this, because well-fitting clothes are simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt, you feel much better than in one of the poles, which is always too high and slippery, standing in the waist, etc.
Young figures can in turn allow themselves to wear clothing with folds, buffs, applications, embroidery or ruffle.
With this amount of information and figure types, I'm glad that I have a whole week to let everything go through my head thoroughly.
And yet, I'm afraid that, given the assigned homework, it's almost impossible.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity to create suitable outfits for - day wear and evening robe.
We should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and its figure type.
I'm supposed to "dress" Miranda Kerr, whom you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
On the inside I cheer, because this is much better for me personally than, for example, putting on Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably increased in recent times to a hundred kilos (well, that's a bit exaggerated), or also the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut out the garments from magazines or search for them on the Internet, print them out and then print them.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, then our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design should be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example trend handbags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about this.
But it's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday presentation filled with information about figure types was seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to exploit this.
And a mailed stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in a very different way.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a t-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heels and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or collar and the whole look looks completely different.
"Play with it," he stressed.
But most of all, the following advice came to mind: "First, you must know the rules perfectly."
"Only then can you hurt her," said Jakub.
At last, I realize why we have to timpani all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see quite different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more clothing variants than he finally photographed.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothes on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes look quite different than in reality.
So you have to expect all of this in the design of the outfit.
Jan Pokorný confirmed that image and styl sometimes make up half of the success.
You just have to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are rather reserved.
Also well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown out money (the main thing is that I bring something as I look secondary).
And if one of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she will most likely force us to a very different (smaller) size than he or she really needs.
Then all you have to do is google to find out for sure that the tabloid press writes that the corresponding celebrity has returned to or decreased, etc.
Jan and Mario encouraged us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "build together" the outfit.
In his work, he must first of all communicate with the people he styles and he must be a cunning psychologist.
Appreciating people without making an offer and standing up to his opinion.
"If any manager orders us to sift through her closet and add some pretty pieces, then we can't clean out the whole closet and tell her - my God, that's terrible."
"You have to find at least a few praiseworthy things to which you recommend what you can contribute," says Mario.
He also showed us very concretely what such a so-called "place bag" must contain.
So this is a bag that you button at the waist and carry all the necessary proprieties with you.
In addition to such clear things as scissors, hair-removing dispensers or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (the stylist helps to photograph products such as handbags or hats), special clips with which the clothes are gathered in the back if they are too large (pins or other clamps are prohibited so that the fabric does not break) and, of course, sewing tools.
But so that we not only have to listen, but can also try something practical, we learned how to glue shoes properly.
Also when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, one can damage the soles of the shoe, let alone the outside.
We were stuck and glued...
With the scissors one must not even touch the shoes, so that one does not damage them.
So you really have to be smart.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned is not exactly my strength.
All this was only a fraction of what we heard at the second weekend continuing course.
One thing has become clear to me now - to devote yourself to styling on a professional level is no child's play.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review
The originally carefree ride becomes a routine journey to the early shift due to a series of completely avoidable, dilettant errors.
Although it succeeded in fulfilling the ambitions to a large extent, what good is that, if obviously no one wanted to do a little more.
Even before he came to the counters, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" raised high expectations.
He promised to move the already year-old game series "Need for Speed" into a new dimension again and in the playable demonstration examples he did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious how the fitted passages would turn out, in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you're used to with NFS, in the end, many things are different than you expected.
Sure - potentially there are quite decent arcade races, but overall the game is diminished by some superfluous mistakes, which have been present in this series more or less for a few years.
So there are actually no more mistakes, but rather signs of a basically incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure begins very well.
First, one is introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain problems of personal character; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, that is, on the west coast, you sit on the wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and in more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race takes place on a different track and that the individual stages take place in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
You don't have a moment to think that game would offer the same thing over and over again.
Some environments are still very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the earlier parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the journey through the desert, through autumnal landscape or high up through deep snowy landscape looks visually very pleasant.
Occasionally, atypical elements bring a little variety to the individual races.
In the desert, for example, one is surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts vision.
In the mountains, on the other hand, one has to be infernally careful that one is not spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are installed quite well in succession.
Only a few, but they're enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classical race against the stopwatch), then you still expect a personal duel with a single opponent.
And there's also the police that's trying to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty is passages in which Jack leaves the car.
This is more about certain interactive animations in which Jack flees from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are much less such passages in the game than one would expect (probably only three).
Ultimately, this is more of a benefit to the matter, because this element at least has no chance of getting bored - it belongs in the context of the above-mentioned to the elements that make the game more varied.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today's point of view, it does not tear out trees, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model continues to do quite well for action-packed racing, although one could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything will be fine.
Real problems only appear after some time.
In contrast to the driving model, the collision model is not entirely O.K.
A game of this kind is hardly to be expected to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have practically no idea how the car behaves before hitting any object, then obviously not everything is fine.
Typical example: In the narrow overtaking or passing of oncoming cars, one "strips" in some places the other cars only slightly, but in other, almost identical situation one gets into spinning and turns wild pirouettes.
Or drive the car right to scrap.
Thanks to the Restart system, it doesn't matter anymore, it's always annoying.
The restarts are solved like this: if you have total damage or land far off the track, then the game throws you back to the last clue of the track.
Only - in each race you only have five Restarts.
Once you've exhausted it, it all starts from the beginning.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something doesn't succeed, but you shouldn't rely on it.
Sometimes, however, even the rest kind does not help, there nothing else but to learn the critical section from the head.
It is extremely unpleasant that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, you have to go through in a very specific way, otherwise you simply don't fit through.
Elsewhere, at the corresponding point, you always encounter "civil" cars in the same configuration, whether you are the first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations when you see that the opponent is passing by two oncoming cars in front of a playful one, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive around them or brake them.
And it doesn't matter when you get there, because everything is designed so that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where you are always overtaken at the same place by the same opponent and here again without regard to the time.
This is the craziest thing to complete the game on the long bridge you pass in the opposite direction.
The opponent obviously has to get you out of here on the devil.
And if he's in front of you, then of course he takes the view, so that you drive your own car a few times in Klump.
Sure - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting but this intention is so clear that it quickly spoils the joy of the game.
And that's a pity, because despite the simpler driving model, the game is generally quite entertaining and sometimes also so action-packed that you almost no longer know where your head is.
And in principle it doesn't matter what is "guilty" about it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no boredom can occur, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the car change in the course of the races.
One should not overlook the petrol stations on the route, because it is precisely here that you can change the car, although in most cases the car is sufficient that you have right now.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
The task mode (challenges) also goes hand in hand with the mode of the game history - i.e. the races in the individual locations known from history.
There are not only medals, but also points of experience to gain for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and the story.
In order to get to the higher driver level, various items need to be opened up: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is at the same time connected with the online function Autolog, which compares among other things its own achieved results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of other unintelligible carvers is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you get by car into a subway tunnel (for my sake), where you race in the dark on the rails long (for my sake).
On the speedometer numerals look between 150 a 200 km/h (for my sake), but suddenly a subway comes from behind and drives an uncompromising to scrap.
In our editorial office, we will probably argue for a long time about whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and here and there even brilliant.
It is all the more annoying that at some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this applies in particular to accidents involving a greater number of people, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound reproduction is OK and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to reach out to a young audience as broad as possible, a soundtrack a lá "of everyone something" was created - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game was not mitigated by the aforementioned totally unnecessary mistakes, we could have claimed with the boob tone of conviction that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But that's how the game seems kind of unfinished.
In itself a great pleasure, but one should be prepared that these mistakes stab you in the eye with the power of airport headlights.
Concert of the "Students of the Velvet Revolution" with vocal ensembles of the Karlsuniversität
The Festival Festa Academica now offers for the third time the combination of the World Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution and this together with the musical experience.
Over the course of the festival, the twenty professional and university choirs will present themselves.
The focus of the festival is on the two concerts, which take place on 17 November.
"Karlsuniversität has a large share in the festival."
"Among the participants is also the choir of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanist Studies, and the festival committee includes the rector Václav Hampl," said Jakub Čaloun, head of the organizing team.
The absolute highlight of the festival is the public concert of technical school choirs, which takes place on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the square in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The programme includes the composition of the important Czech jazz musician Karel Rşıička "Celebration Jazz Mass".
In the evening hours, the concert "Students of the Velvet Revolution" (Studenty Sametu) takes place in the gala rooms of the Volkshaus in Vinohrady, in which also university choirs perform, choirs of the Karlsuniversität are not excluded.
Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate the World Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to promote the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Association of Czech Choirs in cooperation with Johannes-Kepler-Gymnasium.
The patron of the entire event was Bohuslav Svoboda, the Lord Mayor of Prague and Václav Hampl, the Rector of Charles University.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The schedule includes numerous music meetings, student cappanings, matinees and other events in addition to festival concerts.
Detailed information can be found on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz
