Some are double - the same law was submitted to both Congress and Senate - others differ only slightly.
There are at least 15 versions of the compensatory budget change in the Senate alone and another dozen that would "control federal spending".
Some of the laws are also identical, but they give their clients - especially beginners in the Republicans who want to polish up their CVs - the opportunity to brag that they have "written" such a measure.
The Budget Control Act, passed in August, requires both the Senate and Congress to vote on a change in budget balance.
