He was even compared in numbers with Central Park of New York.
With the sinking of the CMB in 1987, the park became, in the eyes of many, the upper limit of Barcelona, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that does not spread in the north-south direction, but up (mountains) and down (sea).
